# Architecture Boundaries Docs

Use `enclosure architecture boundaries` to validate dependency rules and architecture flow from `.enclosure/enclosure.yaml`.

## When To Use It

- After changing imports across modules or layers.
- After moving files between ownership areas.
- Before finishing a refactor that could change dependency direction.

## How To Respond

- Treat reported violations as blockers.
- Prefer depending on a module's public seam instead of private implementation files.
- Move orchestration outward and policy inward when dependency direction is wrong.
- Break cycles by moving shared behavior to the true owner or adding a narrower handoff.

## Related Commands

- `enclosure architecture health --docs`
- `enclosure architecture map --docs`
- `enclosure architecture shape --docs`
